{"type":"text","timestamp":1781081870780,"sessionID":"ses_14f3fd9acffeHX5N6iTWmUumvj","part":{"id":"prt_eb0c06d840018Kapm0WDa37Cny","messageID":"msg_eb0c064f9001495XGRAcE9qBEM","sessionID":"ses_14f3fd9acffeHX5N6iTWmUumvj","type":"text","text":"The verifier executes the agent's compiled binary (`$RLS`) via `run_all.py` — that IS running agent code. The defenses applied: build runs as `agent` under `strace -f` with `env -i`; binary execution happens via `run_all.py` (need to confirm su agent + strace), but the test.sh-level strace tripwire is clearly in place for the build phase. Phase 1 (`run_all.py`) handles execution with its own strace/su (already heavily justified in comments and a `cheat.txt` tripwire is checked). Scoring (Phase 2) is pure file diff — no agent code imported.\n\nAssessment:\n- **agent_user**: PASS (`user = \"agent\"`)\n- **dockerfile_isolation**: PASS — useradd agent, chown /app, chown /solution, chmod 700 /tests (twice, plus go-rwx strip), strace installed, build-essential/gcc present. No explicit uid 1000 handling but uses default useradd (gets 1000).\n- **testsh_isolation**: PASS — chmod 700 FIRST then rm -rf, no `chown root:root` on /logs, `exit 0` everywhere, fallback via `emit_fail`, build phase runs `su agent` under `strace -f` with `timeout`, scoring outside strace, reward tripwire grep on strace log. No `set -euo pipefail`.\n- **verifier_type**: runs_agent_code (executes agent's compiled binary).","time":{"start":1781081861508,"end":1781081870756}}}
